Covering a total area of 164 square kilometers, the Hengshui Lake Wetland connects two cities. Dubbed by some as the "sapphire of East Asia", it is the most comprehensive wetland ecosystem in the North China Plain. Check the video to see more. About 'Journeys in Nature': Hebei series Hebei Province hosts the largest forest park in northern China, Saihanba National Forest Park, and the country's largest expanse of coastal sand dunes, the Golden Coast National Nature Reserve. Here, you will find unique landforms and a rich variety of plants and animals. For more: Hebei series | Episode 1: Beautiful Highland Hebei series | Episode 2: Boundary River Hebei series | Episode 3: Wetland in the Snow Hebei series | Episode 4: The Rhythm of Winter Hebei series | Episode 5: Golden Coast Hebei series | Episode 6: Qilihai (Cover image via a screenshot) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)